The article announces the first round of guests who will be seated in the First Lady's box during the State of the Union Address. The guests include survivors of the Boston Marathon bombing, Carlos Arredondo and Jeff Bauman, who have become friends since the attack. Fire Chief Gary Bird, who led the rescue efforts after a devastating tornado hit Moore, Oklahoma, is also among the guests. Jason Collins, a 12-year NBA player who came out as gay in 2013, will be in the First Lady's box. Joey Hudy, a young inventor and proponent of STEM education, and Kathy Hollowell-Makle, the 2013 DCPS Teacher of the Year, complete the list of guests.